        public StandardIntegrationFlowContext.StandardIntegrationFlowRegistrationBuilder id(String id)
        Specify an id for the IntegrationFlow to register. Must be unique per context. The registration with this id must be destroyed before reusing for a new IntegrationFlow instance.

      • useFlowIdAsPrefix

        public IntegrationFlowContext.IntegrationFlowRegistrationBuilder useFlowIdAsPrefix()
        Description copied from interface: IntegrationFlowContext.IntegrationFlowRegistrationBuilder
        Invoke this method to prefix bean names in the flow with the (required) flow id and a period. This is useful if you wish to register the same flow multiple times while retaining the ability to reference beans within the flow; adding the unique flow id to the bean name makes the name unique.
        Specified by:
        useFlowIdAsPrefix in interface IntegrationFlowContext.IntegrationFlowRegistrationBuilder
        Returns:
        the current builder instance.
